"Steve" == Steve Gardner <gardner@aurora.cc.monash.edu.au> writes:

Steve> As the author of RGB I & II, I can tell you that I regard the
Steve> form that RGB II takes as a self-repealing Rule as a
Steve> regrettably inelegant necessity.

Note that if it is couched in the form of Currency balance
adjustments, it need not be a self-repealing Rule.

Steve> I take it, for instance, that it would be pretty messy
Steve> (although perfectly legal) for a Proposal to create a large
Steve> number of Transfer Orders (in the case of RGB II, one for every
Steve> Player, another one for every Contestmaster, and a few others),
Steve> which individual Players would then have to satisfy by making
Steve> the appropriate Payment Orders.

One, you have it backward: Transfer Orders satisfy Payment Orders.
Two, as other have noted, it is not clear that a Proposal can create a
nomic entity, which means that a Proposal cannot create a Payment
Order, and a Proposal lacks authority to command Players to execute
Payment Orders on its own.  Hence, I do not believe that a Proposal
can, by itself, cause the execution of Payment or Transfer Orders.  I
would somewhat like to see this rectified.

However, P/C will not prevent the use of direct manipulations of
currencies held by entities.  Note, however, that Treasuries will not
exist after P/C (assuming it passes); Players should keep this in mind
when drafting Proposals.

