Don't misunderstand - I'm not saying there should be no such notion as
Nomicality. I am a 'nomizen' of Agora; other Agora Players are nomizens
of various other Nomics in addition. What I was stating was my opposition
to the notion of enacting any Rules that would place different requirements
upon Players, solely based upon the Nomicality, or lack thereof, of the
Players involved. I want to have the right to join a Nomic without having
to state other Nomic-related (or for that matter non-Nomic-related)
affiliations. I should not have to disclose any information about myself
when joining a Nomic other than my name and email address.

> >>I wouldn't like any restriction, however benign in intent, on my
> rights to circulate freely within the Nomic Community.<<
> 
