"Jeffrey" == Jeffrey L Caruso <eljefe@easynet.co.uk> writes:

Jeffrey> You mean that currency reform will mean the end of Rule 1687
Jeffrey> ?? 

It would have been difficult to recast Rule 1687 into the new
paradigm; it violates the principle that units of Currency are only
transferred when their owner causes them to be transferred, amongst
other things.  Furthermore, one of the basic goals of Pragmatic
Currencies is to make Currency Recordkeeping much less error-prone and
far more straightforward.  I do not believe that Rule 1687's measures
are necessary in the paradigm proposed by Pragmatic Currencies.

